  <p>
    So you know how sometimes you’re working on something and you’re not really sure how you got it to work, but you managed to hack it together. If you don’t then you’re probably a programming genius and way smarter than me. Seeing how I’ve been programming for two months, I hack a lot of things until they work. Any who this was the case for the kanomi code that I put in, Scamazon, a group project I was a part of creating for class. I used JavaScript to make text flash on the screen after the user enters in the kanomi code. I figured I’d write a two part blog post going over how I accomplished it
  </p>

  <p>
    I put the text on the home page and wrapped a div around it with the id of ‘kanomi’ and styled it with CSS. After getting the text to appear how I wanted, I set the display property to none and used some JavaScript magic to handle the rest. I found a great kanomi code JS tutorial online from <a href="http://www.yourinspirationweb.com/en/fun-with-javascript-jquery-and-konami-code/">yourinspirationweb.com</a>. 
  </p>

