  <p>
    While this code is still at little bit magic for me. I was able to develop a general and very basic overview of what the code is doing. With the ready function, the code will be executed once the document is finished loading. The variable keys is the empty array that will hold the respective keystrokes that the user types in. The variable konami contains a string of the correct keystrokes to activate the action. 
  </p>

  <p>
    By calling .keydown, the keydown event is sent to an element when the user first presses a key on the keyboard. In this case I think the event is the document. The keydown pass the e function which pushes the keystroke’s value into the variable keys. The if conditional statement converts the keys variable to a string and if it matches the konami string it executes code to make the text appear and disappear. Stay toned for the next post, for the second part of the explanation of how jQuery is used to make the text flash.
  </p>
